<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Snaggletooth:
[B]Thanks for the input, Kerith.  Well thought out.

One thing about the new server...  Well  a lot of stuff I guess.  Can you tell I'm bored?

When my level 30 Eru wizard AE's your entire newbie group on orc hill, and you all begin your corpse runs, will you quit the server?  Will I get a nasty tell?  Or will I get "you sneaky bastard!  You leveled the whole hill! :P"

If I do the same thing the next day, the day after that, and each day for a month, will you put up with it?  Will you live and learn from the trauma?  Or will you quit because the game is broken?

A PKr deals with 'bluebies' daily.  That is why bluebies are on our minds, and we make up cute names for them.  Because they are EVERYWHERE.  Yes, on PvP servers.

A bluebie sends a nasty tell, trying to insult you, after you kill him.  Fungi monk does NOT.  The mutual respect that exists between skilled PKrs revolves around skill, not demographics.

When Fungi monk attempts to kill me and he can't even punch me once because I'm circle strafing in tandem with him, the mutual respect that is formed is a very powerful bond, yet has nothing to do with our personalities.  This is very similar to 2 professional athletes going head to head.  They may hate each other, but they respect each other's skill.

I do not say roxors.

I will be rolling up a wizard on the new PvP server, and I can tell you right now that I am going to be solely responsible for some people quitting the server.  I know I will be.

I truly believe I will be doing the server justice by removing as many bluebies as possible.  Those who escape me, those who learn from dying by my hands, those who kill me, and those who say "nice fight" or nothing at all will be the ones that belong on Laetus Zek.

btw - Don't bother flaming me for having the desire to AE a bunch of noobies.  You all have wanted to nuke some newbie at one time or another.  This server will have no rules and no level limits for a reason.  It's so anyone can do whatever the heck they want to do.

Commiting heinous acts on the new server can hardly be judged.  No one is forced to subject themselves to it.  If it turns out that I am griefed off the server some day by a level 60 Troll, then that's how it will end.  It's his right to do so, and I have no business complaining.

Don't think for a second that bluebies are not playing on the PvP servers.  They are the large majority.

Do you guys like Snaggle's Postulate?   I was thinking of snipping that section and putting it on the main board to see if people agree or disagree with the postulate.  It's not easy to swallow.  It hurts people's pride.  No one wants to think of a PKr extraordinairre as anything other than a kewl d00d who speaks using Werdz like SuXor or r0XX0r, or saying "eye weel keel j00!"[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
